en: [Entries from the Cherokee Supreme Court Docket, 1823-1834, New Echota] 1824 Oct. 26

This is an excerpt from the Cherokee Supreme Court docket for the years 1823 to 1834. The Cherokee Supreme Court convened annually in New Echota beginning on the second Monday in October and lasting three weeks. This excerpt is from the Tuesday October 26, 1824 session of court, during which a plea of default was heard. Entries from this Supreme Court docket cover items ch100-ch163.

body.value: Tuesday 26th Court convened agreeable to adjournment Present their Honors &C et cetera Jurors George Saunders , Foreman Fishing Hawk Ptf Plaintiff vs William Burges Dft Defendant On a plea of default Appeal from Amoiah Amoah District to the Supreme Court It is the opinion of the Court, that William Burges shall pay the Fishing Hawk, forty dollars for his horse Court is adjourned untill until tomorrow 10 Oclock
